            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-03-08 21:46:38" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a person who is a member of the same {L:πατριά&lt;SDBG:πατριά:000001&gt;}[b] or {L:φυλή&lt;SDBG:φυλή:000001&gt;}[b] ‘nation’ ({D:11.56})</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>fellow countryman</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The term ἄνδρες is often added to ἀδελφοί[d], constituting a lexical unit having essentially the same meaning as ἀδελφοί[d], but with the connotation of greater formality: ἄνδρες ἀδελφοίἐξὸν εἰπεῖν μετὰ παρρησίας πρὸς ὑμᾶς ‘fellow countrymen, I can speak to you quite plainly’ {S:04400202900002}.|{L:συμφυλέτης&lt;SDBG:συμφυλέτης:000003&gt;}[d] may often be translated by a phrase, for example, ‘a person of the same country’ or ‘a man who belongs to the same nation’ or ‘one who is part of the same tribe.’</Comments>
